WEBVTT

00:08.216 --> 00:10.301
<i>I am not a woman.</i>

00:10.343 --> 00:12.303
<i>I am an icon.</i>

00:13.847 --> 00:15.724
<i>I am not a woman.</i>

00:16.766 --> 00:19.144
<i>I am an icon.</i>

00:21.354 --> 00:23.231
I am not a woman.

00:24.691 --> 00:27.652
I am an icon.

00:27.694 --> 00:29.154
- Angelyne?

00:31.448 --> 00:32.615
Read it.

00:34.993 --> 00:37.537
- Oh, I don't think
that that's a very good i--

00:37.579 --> 00:38.788
- Read it.

00:41.207 --> 00:42.792
- Okay.

00:42.834 --> 00:47.130
"The mystery of
LA billboard diva Angelyne's

00:47.172 --> 00:50.675
"real identity
is finally solved,"

00:50.717 --> 00:55.847
by Jeff Glaser
of "The Hollywood Reporter."

00:55.889 --> 00:59.559
"Way before Paris Hilton
and Kim Kardashian,

00:59.601 --> 01:02.145
"the enigmatic
blonde bombshell

01:02.187 --> 01:04.773
"was famous for being famous,

01:04.814 --> 01:07.317
"perpetually driving
the streets of Hollywood

01:07.359 --> 01:10.153
"in that pink Corvette,
but her true identity

01:10.195 --> 01:13.990
"has remained secret
all these years...

01:14.032 --> 01:15.700
until now."

02:10.714 --> 02:12.007
- Who is she?

02:15.385 --> 02:16.886
- All right.

02:53.256 --> 02:56.551
<i>- Mysterious billboards are</i>
<i>popping up around the city</i>

02:56.593 --> 02:57.969
<i>featuring the striking image</i>

02:58.011 --> 03:00.055
<i>of a blonde</i>
<i>with a single name,</i>

03:00.096 --> 03:01.556
<i>Angelyne,</i>

03:01.598 --> 03:03.475
<i>raising the question</i>


03:03.516 --> 03:04.893
<i>who is Angelyne,</i>

03:04.934 --> 03:08.063
<i>and what exactly</i>
<i>is she advertising?</i>

03:08.104 --> 03:09.773
- What do I think she does
by looking at it?

03:09.814 --> 03:12.567
- Actually, I did hear that she
was trying to be a star

03:12.609 --> 03:14.444
and that she bought
all these billboards

03:14.486 --> 03:15.779
trying to be a star.
Am I right?

03:15.820 --> 03:17.739
- Angelyne,
why are you famous?

03:17.781 --> 03:20.408
- I'm famous
for being on billboards.

03:20.450 --> 03:22.327
- Angelyne!
<i>- I see her sometimes.</i>

03:22.369 --> 03:23.995
<i>I saw her ride by in her car,</i>

03:24.037 --> 03:26.664
and she was just paying
maximum attention

03:26.706 --> 03:28.458
<i>to the people on the sidewalk,</i>

03:28.500 --> 03:30.168
<i>just, you know, showing up.</i>

03:30.210 --> 03:31.419
- Ooh.

03:31.461 --> 03:34.005
- The one, the only Angelyne.

03:39.469 --> 03:41.262
- Angelyne finally decided

03:41.304 --> 03:43.348
all those billboards
weren't enough,

03:43.390 --> 03:45.266
<i>so she put up</i>
<i>this ten-story-tall</i>

03:45.308 --> 03:46.810
<i>mural of herself</i>

03:46.851 --> 03:48.353
<i>at the corner</i>
<i>of Hollywood and Vine.</i>

03:48.395 --> 03:52.315
It was there for six months
and cost more than $50,000.

03:52.357 --> 03:55.652
<i>- The mystery of Angelyne</i>
<i>has become a media obsession,</i>

03:55.694 --> 03:57.028
although she outright refuses

03:57.070 --> 03:59.781
to tell you anything
about her past.

04:04.285 --> 04:07.664
- People have a lot of opinions
about who you are.

04:07.706 --> 04:10.208
How would you
describe yourself?

04:10.250 --> 04:13.294
- I'm a Rorschach test in pink.

04:13.336 --> 04:15.422
Ooh.

04:15.463 --> 04:17.966
An innocent little doll

04:18.008 --> 04:19.509
or a whore

04:19.551 --> 04:21.344
or a porn star.

04:22.220 --> 04:24.389
People see...

04:24.431 --> 04:26.474
what they see.

04:26.516 --> 04:28.435
- I love Angelyne

04:28.476 --> 04:31.104
for all the same reasons

04:31.146 --> 04:34.774
the extremes, the weirdness,
the glamour, the enigma.

04:34.816 --> 04:37.193
- There's something sexy
about a mystery.

04:37.235 --> 04:40.030
That's why everybody
wants to know my story.

04:40.071 --> 04:41.614
- Back then,
you could still disappear

04:41.656 --> 04:44.117
or reappear as someone else.

04:44.159 --> 04:45.827
You can't really
do that anymore.

04:45.869 --> 04:48.788
Angelyne existed at a point
in American history

04:48.830 --> 04:50.331
when that was still possible.

04:50.373 --> 04:51.833
- Everyone wants
to interview her.

04:51.875 --> 04:54.669
They're doing a story about
the history of Los Angeles.

04:54.711 --> 04:55.837
They're doing a story about

04:55.879 --> 04:58.214
the greatest sex symbols
of our time.

04:58.256 --> 05:00.675
They want
to interview Angelyne.

05:00.717 --> 05:02.385
- Who is Angelyne really?

05:02.427 --> 05:04.512
What's her story?
Where is she from?

05:04.554 --> 05:06.181
That's what I set out to learn,

05:06.222 --> 05:07.557
and I was successful.

05:07.599 --> 05:09.642
- Jeff Glaser
turned out to be...

05:11.394 --> 05:13.646
A liar, and I hate liars.

05:14.898 --> 05:18.068
He was just biting
at the ch--

05:18.109 --> 05:20.195
mm, whatever you call it

05:20.236 --> 05:21.571
to get the story.

05:23.573 --> 05:25.116
- So the story isn't true?

05:36.086 --> 05:38.546
- Hey, Jeff,
here are those photos

05:38.588 --> 05:41.049
you asked for of Angelyne.

05:41.091 --> 05:42.509
- Thank you.

05:42.550 --> 05:45.887
- Yeah, she was in a band
called Baby Blue in the '70s.

05:45.929 --> 05:48.932
That guy's name right there
is Cory Hunt.

05:48.973 --> 05:51.059
- Cory?

05:51.101 --> 05:53.061
Oh.

05:54.979 --> 05:56.231
Cory's dead.

05:56.272 --> 05:57.941
- I am not dead.

05:59.317 --> 06:00.944
Of course
she would say that, man.

06:00.985 --> 06:02.404
You know why
she would say that?

06:02.445 --> 06:05.448
Because I created Angelyne.

06:08.952 --> 06:12.247
Does she know
you're talking to me?

06:12.288 --> 06:13.998
- Did I say Cory was dead?

06:15.667 --> 06:17.419
Well, he doesn't live
in LA anymore.

06:17.460 --> 06:20.130
I sometimes
get the two confused.

06:20.171 --> 06:22.007
- God's honest truth?

06:22.048 --> 06:24.968
This whole Angelyne story
starts with me.

06:26.720 --> 06:29.264
She was nothing before me.

06:58.835 --> 07:01.463
- He's probably gonna
tell you some story

07:01.504 --> 07:05.342
about how he saved me
or discovered me,

07:05.383 --> 07:06.968
and if that'll make him happy,
he can do that.

07:07.010 --> 07:08.303
But the truth is,
when I met him,

07:08.345 --> 07:12.640
I was already quite busy
modeling and acting.

07:12.682 --> 07:15.477
But the characters
weren't reflective

07:15.518 --> 07:19.731
of who I am on the inside,
so...

07:19.773 --> 07:22.067
I had a different plan.

07:27.030 --> 07:30.658
<i>- I was looking for a band</i>
<i>that wasn't going anywhere,</i>

07:30.700 --> 07:32.494
<i>one that I could mold.</i>

07:32.535 --> 07:34.079
<i>That's how I discovered him.</i>

07:34.120 --> 07:35.747
Coca-Cola, please.

07:37.749 --> 07:40.001
<i>- They were nothing much</i>
<i>to look at,</i>

07:40.043 --> 07:42.253
<i>but that's okay,</i>
<i>'cause no one was looking.</i>

07:43.380 --> 07:45.006
<i>I will never forget</i>
<i>that night.</i>

07:45.048 --> 07:47.342
<i>We had a residency</i>
<i>at the Starwood.</i>

07:47.384 --> 07:49.844
<i>We were already gaining</i>
<i>a ton of buzz.</i>

07:49.886 --> 07:52.555
<i>There was cosmic energy</i>
<i>in the air that night.</i>

07:57.936 --> 08:00.188
We have been
and we will always be

08:00.230 --> 08:01.940
Baby Blue.

08:01.981 --> 08:04.109
Thank you, and good night.

08:04.150 --> 08:05.193
- You guys rip, man!

08:05.235 --> 08:06.695
- Hey, Cory, great show.

08:06.736 --> 08:09.864
- Mm-hmm.

08:09.906 --> 08:12.033
<i>- And that's</i>
<i>when I discovered her,</i>

08:12.075 --> 08:16.287
<i>this divine creature</i>
<i>from outer space.</i>

08:18.456 --> 08:20.041
I'll be right back.

08:20.083 --> 08:23.545
<i>I never saw anything</i>
<i>so beautiful.</i>

08:28.258 --> 08:30.552
So what did you think
of the band?

08:30.593 --> 08:32.470
- What band?

08:32.512 --> 08:34.389
- Mine.

08:34.431 --> 08:35.890
We were just onstage.

08:35.932 --> 08:38.101
- Oh, was that you?
I wasn't listening.

08:38.143 --> 08:39.728
How'd you do?

08:39.769 --> 08:41.271
- We were incredible.

08:44.441 --> 08:45.734
We were fine.

08:45.775 --> 08:47.819
- If you're aiming
for just fine,

08:47.861 --> 08:50.947
you'll probably end up
just missing it.

08:50.989 --> 08:52.574
You gotta aim higher.

08:52.615 --> 08:53.575
- Yeah, I know.

08:53.616 --> 08:56.077
I mean, this place is not bad,

08:56.119 --> 08:58.538
but we really should be
playing the Whisky.

08:58.580 --> 09:01.875
- Then you gotta play every
show as if it's the Whisky,

09:01.916 --> 09:03.668
and one day...

09:03.710 --> 09:04.836
It will be.

09:06.296 --> 09:07.672
- Can I buy you a drink?

09:07.714 --> 09:09.049
- I don't drink...

09:10.425 --> 09:11.926
Or smoke.

09:13.720 --> 09:14.971
- Who are you?

09:16.598 --> 09:18.099
- Angelyne.

09:19.434 --> 09:21.811
Yeah, my dad, right,

09:21.853 --> 09:23.730
he's got this whole
Soviet work ethic

09:23.772 --> 09:25.940
where you just work
your whole life

09:25.982 --> 09:28.109
and you expect nothing,

09:28.151 --> 09:30.320
but I say what's the point
of living if you aren't...

09:30.362 --> 09:31.613
Following your dreams.

09:31.654 --> 09:34.115
- Yeah, yeah.

09:34.157 --> 09:38.078
Yeah, so I said, "No,
I'm not gonna live like that."

09:38.119 --> 09:39.829
So I packed up all my shit.

09:39.871 --> 09:41.456
I fled to LA,

09:41.498 --> 09:42.957
started a band.

09:42.999 --> 09:46.044
I mean, I've played every club
around here.

09:46.086 --> 09:49.631
Eventually I'm gonna
play the Whisky.

09:49.673 --> 09:52.092
That'll prove him wrong,
you know?

09:53.051 --> 09:56.721
- Fathers can ruin your life.

09:57.555 --> 10:00.475
- So what about you?
Are you close with your dad?

10:00.517 --> 10:03.561
- Oh, I never knew him.
He died when I was a baby.

10:03.603 --> 10:04.854
- Oh.

10:06.147 --> 10:07.440
I'm sorry.

10:08.650 --> 10:10.026
Your mom?

10:11.444 --> 10:13.071
- What's your sign?

10:14.447 --> 10:15.532
- Aquarius.

10:17.158 --> 10:19.536
- No wonder you're a rebel.

10:19.577 --> 10:21.496
- Hey, wait.
Where you going?

10:21.538 --> 10:23.206
- Home, of course.

10:26.042 --> 10:28.586
- She'd occasionally
share things about herself

10:28.628 --> 10:30.130
to gain sympathy,
but when it comes

10:30.171 --> 10:32.757
it the actual truth
about her past,

10:32.799 --> 10:35.343
no, she never went there.

10:35.385 --> 10:37.345
Hey, hey, wait up.

10:37.387 --> 10:39.806
You know how many freaks
and weirdos are out here?

10:39.848 --> 10:41.558
You could get
your head chopped off.

10:41.599 --> 10:44.769
- Don't worry, Daddy.
I'm stronger than I look.

10:44.811 --> 10:46.479
- No, but you--

10:46.521 --> 10:47.939
- You shouldn't be walking.

10:47.981 --> 10:49.357
Hey, I work at a garage.

10:49.399 --> 10:52.277
I could help you
get a cheap car if you want.

10:52.318 --> 10:54.279
- Oh, I don't want
just any car.

10:54.320 --> 10:57.699
A car is supposed to be
an extension of you,

10:57.741 --> 10:59.034
your being.

10:59.075 --> 11:01.036
I want something fast

11:01.077 --> 11:04.164
so I can get away if I have to.

11:04.205 --> 11:06.124
- What would you need
to get away from?

11:07.459 --> 11:09.711
- Anyone, anything,

11:09.753 --> 11:11.504
I have to know I can escape.

11:12.839 --> 11:14.716
That's why I'm saving up
to buy my dream car,

11:14.758 --> 11:18.136
my very own Star 'Vette.

11:18.178 --> 11:19.763
- Star 'Vette.
- Mm-hmm.

11:21.097 --> 11:22.891
That's what Barbie
calls her Corvette,

11:22.932 --> 11:24.392
her dream machine.

11:26.519 --> 11:29.773
- Barbie the doll?

11:29.814 --> 11:31.900
- The American icon.

11:31.941 --> 11:35.195
I'd love to be like Barbie.

11:35.236 --> 11:38.656
- You're already blonde
and beautiful.

11:38.698 --> 11:40.909
- Oh, she's so much more
than that.

11:40.950 --> 11:43.578
