every night at 10:00 p.m.

16:56.891 --> 17:00.520
to dye her hair
and take a bubble bath.

17:02.313 --> 17:04.232
She's a lot, man.

17:04.274 --> 17:07.235
- Yeah, but do we need
a singer?

17:07.277 --> 17:09.237
- We need her.

17:09.279 --> 17:12.240
- We need her or you need her?

17:12.282 --> 17:14.617
- Hey, guys,
I think we're being watched.

17:14.659 --> 17:17.662
- Hey, hey, don't worry.
Honestly, she's moldable.

17:17.704 --> 17:19.873
We just--we'll put her
where we want to put her.

17:19.914 --> 17:21.332
She's eye candy.

17:21.374 --> 17:23.835
All right, crowds will
eat that shit up.

17:23.877 --> 17:27.589
<i>- I met Cory a few years</i>
<i>before he met Angelyne.</i>

17:27.630 --> 17:30.508
Yeah, I remember he said he
went to Berklee School of Music

17:30.550 --> 17:32.677
but he left
because he was too good.

17:34.888 --> 17:36.097
Too good.

17:36.139 --> 17:39.225
Oh, but still, he had
true God-given talent.

17:41.019 --> 17:43.146
